    {
      "name": "Jeremy Combes",
      "type": "bond",
      "system": {
        "name": "",
        "description": "<p>She met Jeremy Combes, a USAAF officer, while serving in the Phillipines, and after the war they moved to Hawai'i together, where they were married in early 1947 and she received a degree in East Asian languages from the University of Hawai'i.</p><p>Jeremy began to spend more time in California towards the end of her studies as he began to function as a USAF liason with the JPL on the subjects of experimental aircraft and future air strategies. When Lily graduated in 1949, she moved to California as well and through her WAC connections found work as a research assistant at the Space and Missile Systems Center working on LORAN station synchronization improvements.</p><p>When the Korean War started, Jeremy was sent to Korea, but was able to coordinate a secretarial position at the JPL for Lily.</p>",
        "score": 13,
        "relationship": "Marriage",
        "hasBeenDamagedSinceLastHomeScene": false
      },
